<exercise checkit-seed="0000" checkit-slug="F1" checkit-title="Simple Interest">
    <statement>
                <p> 
                    Blanca took out a short term small business loan of $3,600. The loan accrues simple interest at an annual interest rate of 14%, and the time period of the loan is 14 months. Blanca plans to pay the loan back all at once at the end of the 14 months.
                    <ol>
                        <li> How much interest does the loan generate over the 14 months? </li>
                        <li> How much will Blanca have to pay off at the end of the loan?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
       
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li> The loan generates <m>I = P_0 r t = 3600(0.14\cdot \frac{14}{12}) =</m>$588.0 in interest.</li>
                <li> They will need to pay 3,600 + 588.0 = $4,188.0 at the end of the loan.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
